From 1792828cffada89338f2bc7e42fa470353505960 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 12:20:55 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 07/17] fix(concall): industrial KPIs, capex guidance,
 table-noise filter, boilerplate strip
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

After Aeroflex test the extractor showed 5 real bugs:

1. Industrials/Capital Goods sector had ZERO KPI keyword patterns —
   'Order Inflow', 'Order Book / Backlog', 'Execution / Revenue',
   'Export Order Mix' all stuck at '○ not extracted' even though
   the deck literally listed export mix tables and capacity numbers.
   Add pattern entries for those plus 'Capex Plan',
   'Capacity Utilization', and Real Estate / Energy KPIs that were
   also missing.

2. inferGuidance only matched US-style 'raised guidance' / 'lowered
   guidance' wording. Indian decks routinely say 'plans to scale up
   to 15,000 skids by Q2FY27' or 'set up automatic welding station
   by Dec-26' — concrete forward plans without explicit raise/lower
   keywords. Added planRe / expansionRe / setupRe; when they fire,
   direction = 'introduced'. Commentary harvest broadened to capture
   sentences with 'on track', 'targeted', 'by Q[N]FY[YY]', 'capacity
   expansion'.

3. Top-quote scoring rewarded numbers but didn't penalize numeric
   tables. Aeroflex deck dumped P&L columns as continuous text and
   one of those rows scored higher than real prose. Add isTableNoise
   check (≥4 numbers + ≤4 prose words ⇒ reject) and isBoilerplate
   check (cover-letter / SEBI safe-harbor markers ⇒ reject), both
   gate with -100 score so they never surface.

4. Cover-letter boilerplate ('To, The General Manager …', SEBI safe-
   harbor paragraph, 'Trading Symbol: AEROFLEX', 'Yours faithfully')
   was scoring fine because it has real verbs and punctuation. Strip
   it out before sentence splitting via stripBoilerplate(); cuts
   text from the start to the first 'Investor Presentation Q[N]
   FY[YY]' / 'Performance Highlights' / 'MD's Commentary' marker.

5. Topic regex matched short non-prose fragments ('FY21 FY22 FY23
   FY24 +25%' was returned as the inflation topic). Replace span
   matching with sentence matching scored by scoreSentence — must
   have ≥1 verb, ≥8 prose words, and pass the table/boilerplate
   filters.

Aeroflex re-test should now show:
 - Concall / Guidance: ● available (capex/capacity plans matched)
 - Sector KPIs: Order Book / Capex Plan / Export Mix / EBITDA Margin
   flip from ○ to ● mentioned in concall
 - Top quotes: cover letter and table dumps removed; MD commentary
   on liquid cooling and capacity expansion at the top
 - Topical Mentions: capex, launches, demand quotes are sentences,
   not chart headers

